WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:59.620 --> 02:00.686
- Do you have any money?
- Um...

02:00.788 --> 02:02.521
That's okay.

02:08.696 --> 02:10.095
Brandon, look.

02:14.802 --> 02:16.201
Where do you think that is?

02:18.973 --> 02:20.939
It's just a model, Darcy.

02:21.976 --> 02:24.009
It's not a real place.

02:24.111 --> 02:25.978
I bet it's Ireland.

02:26.080 --> 02:29.548
Mom said Christmas is beautiful
in Ireland.

02:29.650 --> 02:32.317
Someday I'll have a Christmas
just like that.

02:34.388 --> 02:36.388
Everything will be perfect.

02:57.111 --> 02:59.178
Okay, Michelangelo,
it's a Christmas card.

02:59.280 --> 03:01.713
- Not the Sistine Chapel.
- It's not done.

03:01.815 --> 03:02.748
You never think it's done,

03:02.850 --> 03:04.683
but it's always gorgeous.

03:04.785 --> 03:05.717
You can touch it up
in Photoshop.

03:05.819 --> 03:07.352
Not the same.

03:07.454 --> 03:09.788
You'll be signing one of these
cards at my funeral.

03:09.890 --> 03:12.224
You could try singing me
a Christmas carol.

03:12.326 --> 03:14.693
It might get me in the mood,
get me to work faster.

03:14.795 --> 03:18.297
Singing is for those
with a joyful inner voice.

03:18.399 --> 03:19.932
I don't have one of those.

03:20.034 --> 03:22.734
Of course you do.
You just need to nurture it.

03:22.836 --> 03:24.436
Mm-hmm,
don't change the subject.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.538
That should have been
to the copywriter an hour ago.

03:26.640 --> 03:28.907
Tom's there until two o'clock
today, I checked.

03:29.009 --> 03:30.042
That's something else
you've been taking

03:30.144 --> 03:31.643
your sweet time with.

03:31.745 --> 03:34.613
It'll happen
if it's supposed to.

03:34.715 --> 03:37.716
Oh, hi, Tom. No one
here was talking about you.

03:39.753 --> 03:41.853
I was just telling Carmen

03:41.956 --> 03:46.592
how I, uh, I-I need to get this
done for you.

03:46.694 --> 03:48.994
- Oh.
- Very soon.

03:49.096 --> 03:51.430
Darcy, I love how much detail
you put in your work.

03:51.532 --> 03:53.198
I can almost
hear those carolers singing.

03:53.300 --> 03:56.735
- It just needs a little more--
- Lil' more shading on the tree.

03:57.905 --> 04:00.138
Yeah, exactly.

04:00.241 --> 04:03.208
Well, perfection
is worth waiting for.

04:05.179 --> 04:07.446
Just drop that in my office
whenever you're done.

04:07.548 --> 04:08.547
Okay.

04:09.149 --> 04:10.215
Carmen.

04:15.089 --> 04:18.123
Okay, you stalled long enough
to get him to come up here.

04:18.225 --> 04:19.690
No, it's really not done.

04:19.793 --> 04:21.827
Perfect is the enemy
of done.

04:21.928 --> 04:24.196
Darcy, tomorrow is Thanksgiving.

04:24.298 --> 04:25.430
The official gateway

04:25.532 --> 04:29.034
to the glorious
Christmas season.

04:29.136 --> 04:31.270
During which
you will make yourself crazy

04:31.372 --> 04:33.305
attempting to achieve
the impossible goal

04:33.407 --> 04:34.706
of a perfect Christmas.

04:34.808 --> 04:37.943
Not impossible.
I just haven't done it yet.

04:38.045 --> 04:40.612
I will see you tomorrow.
Five o'clock sharp.

05:09.576 --> 05:12.144
Hey, Brandon. Happy
Thanksgiving. You almost here?

05:12.246 --> 05:13.979
Uh, I'm about
to head into the store.

05:14.081 --> 05:15.814
Tell me again, what kind
of cheese I'm supposed to get.

05:15.916 --> 05:18.383
The gouda kind, the bada kind?

05:18.485 --> 05:20.319
Oh, speaking of cheesy.

05:20.421 --> 05:22.988
<i>- So Kraft Singles then?</i>
- Not funny.

05:23.090 --> 05:25.057
My first-choice cheese
is the herbed goat cheese,

05:25.159 --> 05:27.025
but if they don't have that,
then just get a plain one.

05:27.127 --> 05:28.660
<i> I definitely</i>
<i>do not want a goat cheese</i>

05:28.762 --> 05:30.562
<i>that was rolled in fruit
or something.</i>

05:30.664 --> 05:32.264
If you do get the plain one,
then I want

05:32.366 --> 05:33.899
another herbed cheese

05:34.001 --> 05:35.267
<i>like a-a dill havarti,</i>

05:35.369 --> 05:36.335
<i>but if you get
the herbed cheese,</i>

05:36.437 --> 05:37.369
<i>then I want smoked gouda</i>

05:37.471 --> 05:38.770
<i>for counterpoint.</i>

05:38.872 --> 05:41.106
Darce,
dinner is gonna be great.

05:41.208 --> 05:43.375
Your parents
will get along fine.

05:43.477 --> 05:45.043
Thanks, Brandon. And hurry.

05:48.682 --> 05:51.083
- Darcy, I'm here.
- Hi, mom.

05:52.853 --> 05:55.253
- Hello, hello.
- Oh, hi.

05:55.356 --> 05:58.390
- So who's coming?
- Um, dad, of course.

05:58.492 --> 06:01.293
And Carmen, and Brandon.

06:01.395 --> 06:04.529
When are you going to give
that nice Brandon a chance?

06:04.631 --> 06:06.264
As I've discussed with you
many times,

06:06.367 --> 06:07.966
Brandon and I are just friends.

06:08.068 --> 06:09.868
Better than being alone
coming up on Christmas.

06:09.970 --> 06:11.737
I want more than to just
not be alone.

06:11.839 --> 06:12.938
I want to be
with the right person.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.740
Like my copywriter, Tom.

06:14.842 --> 06:16.808
He appreciates
my attention to detail.

06:16.910 --> 06:19.578
He is the sort of person
I should be with.

06:19.680 --> 06:22.614
You let too many shoulds
run your life, Darcy.

06:22.716 --> 06:24.383
Mom, I know
you're full of opinions,

06:24.485 --> 06:26.084
but you don't actually
have to say them all out loud.

06:26.186 --> 06:28.086
It's how I show that I care.

06:28.188 --> 06:29.454
So did you bring the pie?

06:29.556 --> 06:32.457
Did I what?
Wait till you try these.

06:32.559 --> 06:34.893
This bakery got
a five-star Yelp review.

06:34.995 --> 06:39.297
Oh, uh, I thought you were gonna
make grandma's recipe.

06:39.400 --> 06:42.434
I know, but every year you tell
me I've done something wrong,

06:42.536 --> 06:44.569
so I thought, you know,
if I brought this,

06:44.671 --> 06:47.272
they'd be perfect,
like you want them.

06:47.374 --> 06:48.940
Okay, uh, that's, that's not
what I, I meant, but--

06:49.042 --> 06:50.976
I bring the best pies
in the city

06:51.078 --> 06:52.978
and they're still not
good enough for you.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.413
Fine, I suppose
I'll just throw them away.

06:54.515 --> 06:56.681
No, no, no,
I'm sure it'll be delicious.

06:56.784 --> 06:58.283
- You have great taste.
- Thank you.

06:58.385 --> 07:00.485
Thank you for the pie.

07:00.587 --> 07:01.686
Hey, hey, hey!

07:04.024 --> 07:05.590
Why can you not have
two Thanksgivings

07:05.692 --> 07:07.459
like any other normal child
of divorce?

07:07.561 --> 07:09.127
Because my wonderful parents
are so mature,

07:09.229 --> 07:11.430
they can handle the occasional
holiday meal together.

07:11.532 --> 07:15.267
Hi, dad. Happy Thanksgiving.

07:15.369 --> 07:16.501
I brought
the green-bean casserole.

07:16.603 --> 07:19.638
- I just need to put it together.
- Oh.

07:19.740 --> 07:21.506
Uh, okay.

07:23.210 --> 07:25.010
Bill, you're not helping.

07:25.112 --> 07:26.845
Oh, Darcy doesn't mind.
Do you, kiddo?

07:26.947 --> 07:29.147
Hey. Happy Thanksgiving.

07:29.249 --> 07:30.348
- Hi.
- Hey-hey-hey.

07:30.451 --> 07:31.817
Uh, I got a little more

07:31.919 --> 07:33.618
than you asked for.

07:35.322 --> 07:38.023
- Oh, Brandon. Brandon.
- Happy Thanksgiving.

07:38.125 --> 07:40.025
- Happy Thanksgiving.
- How are you?

07:40.127 --> 07:42.160
- Hey, Bill.
- Hey.

07:42.262 --> 07:44.362
- Hey, how you doing?
- All right. Good to see you.

07:44.465 --> 07:46.565
- Happy Thanksgiving.
- Happy Thanksgiving.

07:52.840 --> 07:54.172
I have no idea
what she asked for.

07:54.274 --> 07:55.874
Kiddo, is there supposed to be

07:55.976 --> 07:57.609
smoke coming out of the oven?

07:57.711 --> 08:00.979
What? No. No, no, no, no.

08:02.816 --> 08:04.783
- Oh.
- Ooh.

08:14.161 --> 08:15.760
Cheer up, Darce.

08:15.863 --> 08:18.730
It's still delicious.

08:18.832 --> 08:20.732
Well, like 90 percent
of it's delicious, you know?

08:20.834 --> 08:23.001
Holiday disappointment
is inevitable.

08:23.103 --> 08:24.936
Well, if every holiday
went perfectly,

08:25.038 --> 08:26.171
how would we ever
tell them apart?

08:26.273 --> 08:28.607
Oh, I gave up on perfect
years ago.

08:28.709 --> 08:30.675
Every time I try to make
something perfect,

08:30.777 --> 08:32.244
it always turned out wrong.

08:32.346 --> 08:34.279
Oh, like the time
we had spaghetti and meatballs

08:34.381 --> 08:36.280
for Thanksgiving,
because you forgot to mention

08:36.383 --> 08:38.015
that you invited your cousins
to swing by.

08:38.118 --> 08:39.918
Hey, that was fun.

08:40.020 --> 08:41.886
Just as
I'm putting out the turkey

08:41.989 --> 08:43.788
for the three of us,
up rolled an RV

08:43.890 --> 08:46.291
with a dozen starved cousins
expecting dinner.

08:46.393 --> 08:47.893
So, back to the kitchen for me.

08:47.995 --> 08:49.961
That Thanksgiving
was complete chaos.

08:50.063 --> 08:51.396
You two were so mad
at each other.

08:51.498 --> 08:53.431
Well, in those days
it wasn't a holiday

08:53.534 --> 08:55.467
unless we were
at each other's throats.

08:55.569 --> 08:58.236
- Holiday traditions are weird.
- That's not what I meant.

08:58.338 --> 09:00.138
Well, like,
it's just not Christmas for me

09:00.240 --> 09:02.908
without this hideous
inflatable Santa Claus

09:03.010 --> 09:05.377
wearing Bermuda shorts.

09:05.479 --> 09:07.746
I hated it for years, but my dad
thought it was hilarious

09:07.848 --> 09:09.881
and now
it's my Christmas tradition.

09:09.983 --> 09:11.583
For my mother it wasn't
Christmas unless we played

09:11.685 --> 09:13.218
her Christmas album.

09:13.320 --> 09:15.287
She's leaving out
that it is one hundred percent

09:15.389 --> 09:18.323
in Gaelic. No idea
what they were saying. Hah.

09:18.425 --> 09:20.258
And the singing's
a wee bit off-key.

09:20.360 --> 09:23.995
But she loved us, so she
tortured us with it every year.

09:24.097 --> 09:27.232
Bill and I loathed it,
but when she passed,

09:27.334 --> 09:28.767
I couldn't bring myself
to throw it out.

09:28.869 --> 09:30.268
I wish I could have a Christmas
like you did

09:30.370 --> 09:31.570
when you were a kid in Ireland.

09:31.672 --> 09:34.673
They weren't all that great,
Darcy.

09:34.775 --> 09:36.841
It just seems like the way
Christmas should be.

09:36.944 --> 09:38.810
One of my favorite Christmases
gone wrong

09:38.912 --> 09:41.012
was when our flight got grounded
in Buffalo.

09:41.114 --> 09:42.247
When we were on our way home
from--

09:42.349 --> 09:44.316
Yeah, our semester abroad.

09:45.552 --> 09:46.685
We had to sleep on our backpacks

09:46.787 --> 09:48.286
because all the hotels
were full.

09:48.388 --> 09:50.088
And there was no food
because the supply trucks

09:50.190 --> 09:52.123
couldn't get through
the ten feet of snow.

09:52.225 --> 09:56.461
Oh, and the s-stupid Oompah band
kept playing polkas...

09:56.563 --> 09:58.096
It was the worst Christmas ever.

09:58.198 --> 10:01.633
Huh, what? No, come on,
that was like one of my best.

10:01.735 --> 10:04.069
You have a really odd sense
of fun, Brandon.

10:07.608 --> 10:10.108
I just want a perfect holiday.
Just once.

10:10.210 --> 10:12.944
One time
where nothing went wrong.

10:13.046 --> 10:15.647
That's just not real life,
Darcy.

10:15.749 --> 10:17.515
A girl can dream, I guess.

10:19.052 --> 10:20.952
Well, I'm exhausted.

10:21.054 --> 10:23.188
I don't know how you're gonna
stay up all night.

10:23.290 --> 10:25.123
There's only two hours
until midnight.

10:25.225 --> 10:27.993
12:01, and then it's officially
the day after Thanksgiving

10:28.095 --> 10:29.628
and the Christmas decorating
begins.

10:29.730 --> 10:30.962
It's still
the day after Thanksgiving

10:31.064 --> 10:31.997
in the morning, you know?

10:32.099 --> 10:33.898
It's tradition.

10:34.001 --> 10:36.534
Well, I know how important
decorating is to you, kiddo,

10:36.637 --> 10:38.637
so I will get out of your hair.

10:38.739 --> 10:40.171
- I'll stay and help.
- Oh, good.

10:40.273 --> 10:43.074
I've got some heavy boxes
for you to drag out.

10:43.176 --> 10:44.676
- Thanks, Darce.
- I love you.

10:44.778 --> 10:46.277
That was delicious,
despite the turkey.

10:46.380 --> 10:48.413
Oh. Well, I tried.

10:52.986 --> 10:55.086
That was a really fun night.

10:55.188 --> 10:58.056
Your parents only sniped
at each other three times.

10:58.158 --> 10:59.557
Total win.

10:59.660 --> 11:02.060
It is a pretty good record
for them, huh?

11:02.162 --> 11:05.730
Okay. Point me to the heavy
things that need lifting.

11:05.832 --> 11:08.099
- It's not time yet.
- Oh, come on, be a rebel.

11:08.201 --> 11:09.934
- Let's start early.
- No. We can't.

11:10.037 --> 11:13.004
It's still Thanksgiving,
it's not right.

11:13.106 --> 11:15.040
Yeah, you're right,
the, uh, Christmas police

11:15.142 --> 11:16.508
could find out, huh?

11:16.610 --> 11:18.109
Oh.

11:18.211 --> 11:20.545
Okay, compromise.

11:20.647 --> 11:22.280
We take out the boxes now,

11:22.382 --> 11:25.283
but we don't open them
until midnight.

11:25.385 --> 11:27.285
Deal?

11:27.387 --> 11:28.753
12:01.

11:29.322 --> 11:30.922
Deal.

11:31.024 --> 11:32.357
But we cannot do any decorating

11:32.459 --> 11:35.193
without the proper regalia.

11:38.498 --> 11:42.634
A <i> My Favorite Things</i> mercantile.

11:42.736 --> 11:44.903
Every village needs one,
am I right?

11:45.005 --> 11:47.872
Where else would you get
your warm, woolen mittens?

11:47.974 --> 11:51.376
Or your schnitzel
with noodles. Oh.

11:51.478 --> 11:57.615
Maybe in Pub.

11:57.718 --> 12:00.452
Oh, only the classics
served in Pub.

12:00.554 --> 12:05.223
Oh, this is too cute!

12:05.325 --> 12:08.059
Okay. I'd live here.
I claim this as my house.

12:08.161 --> 12:11.930
Uh, n-n-no.
That is where I live.

12:12.032 --> 12:14.899
Ouch. So I'm homeless.

12:15.001 --> 12:19.504
No. You would live here.

12:19.606 --> 12:22.941
Hm, well, uh, uh, do I at least
get to pick where it goes?

12:23.043 --> 12:25.543
No! No. No, that's my job.

12:26.780 --> 12:28.613
Okay, boss.

12:28.715 --> 12:32.684
Uh... where does this go?

12:33.954 --> 12:37.155
Um, here.

12:37.257 --> 12:39.924
And what about this guy?

12:40.026 --> 12:43.328
- Ooh, ooh, careful.
- I'm being careful.

12:43.430 --> 12:46.998
He goes right here.

12:47.100 --> 12:50.468
Isn't it a little boring, doing
it the same way every year?

12:50.570 --> 12:54.205
I mean, you have almost
infinite possibilities here.

12:54.307 --> 12:56.174
We could try some of them.

12:56.276 --> 12:59.444
This is how I want it.

12:59.546 --> 13:01.112
How do you know what you want
if you haven't tried

13:01.214 --> 13:02.680
all the options?

13:02.783 --> 13:06.117
Because this way works.
This way makes sense.

13:06.219 --> 13:09.053
You know, nothing bad
will happen

13:09.156 --> 13:11.890
if you change something.

13:11.992 --> 13:13.892
Why does anything
have to change?

13:13.994 --> 13:17.896
Well, because life is change.

13:17.998 --> 13:20.198
And that's why my Christmas
village doesn't, okay?

13:20.300 --> 13:23.968
I don't have control over life!
I have control over this...

13:24.070 --> 13:26.037
Why are you being so weird
about this?

13:26.139 --> 13:27.539
This is something
I look forward to every year,

13:27.641 --> 13:30.475
and you're ruining it.

13:30.577 --> 13:32.010
Ruining it? Great. Okay.

13:32.112 --> 13:34.712
Well, I thought
I was part of your fun,

13:34.815 --> 13:37.916
but if not, I'll just go home.

13:38.018 --> 13:39.984
See you later, Darcy.

13:41.955 --> 13:44.522
Brandon, wait. Oh...

13:46.159 --> 13:47.325
Oh, no.

14:59.399 --> 15:01.900
How did I not know
this place was still around?

15:03.770 --> 15:06.337
This is where I first fell
in love with Christmas villages.

15:06.439 --> 15:10.541
- We do keep unusual hours.
- Uh, yeah, it's...

15:10.644 --> 15:12.143
It's 2:00 in the morning.

15:12.245 --> 15:14.946
Well, it is the day
after Thanksgiving.

15:15.048 --> 15:17.382
Officially,
the start of Christmas season.

15:18.952 --> 15:20.218
That's what I always say.

15:21.421 --> 15:24.889
So what are you missing?

15:27.661 --> 15:30.995
- What?
- From your Christmas village.

15:31.097 --> 15:35.867
Oh. Well,
I broke my post office.

15:35.969 --> 15:37.535
You can't have
a perfect Christmas village

15:37.637 --> 15:40.004
with no post office.

15:40.106 --> 15:41.706
Do you have an Irish one?

15:44.277 --> 15:46.644
I've got one right here.

15:47.414 --> 15:48.479
Oh.

15:49.416 --> 15:50.815
It's perfect.

15:50.917 --> 15:53.651
I'll take it. Thank you.

15:53.753 --> 15:54.886
When I was a little girl

15:54.988 --> 15:58.056
and things weren't so great
at home,

15:58.158 --> 16:00.825
I used to come here and stare
at the Christmas villages.

16:00.927 --> 16:04.195
I dreamed of a place
where all your worries were gone

16:04.297 --> 16:07.231
and it was the perfect
Irish Christmas.

16:07.334 --> 16:11.035
You know, uh, I have
some one-of-a-kind pieces.

16:11.137 --> 16:12.236
Over here.

16:18.812 --> 16:20.878
She looks just like me.

16:20.981 --> 16:24.015
She'd be right at home
in your Irish Christmas village.

16:24.117 --> 16:27.952
- How much?
- For you, it's on the house.

16:28.054 --> 16:29.454
- Really?
- Hm.

16:30.156 --> 16:31.422
Thank you.

16:31.524 --> 16:34.158
It's my pleasure.

16:34.260 --> 16:36.294
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

16:59.786 --> 17:02.186
Here's to a perfect Christmas.

17:17.337 --> 17:19.569
Alexa, turn off alarm.

17:25.811 --> 17:27.678
What?

17:30.717 --> 17:32.417
Did I take an Ambien
last night?

18:04.951 --> 18:07.085
- Merry Christmas, love.
- Merry Christmas, love.

18:09.589 --> 18:11.823
Hot chocolate.
With a bit of whipped cream.

18:11.925 --> 18:14.559
Just the way you like it.

18:14.661 --> 18:16.294
Why are you two together?

18:16.396 --> 18:18.996
And smiling and...

18:19.099 --> 18:20.498
Why are you talking like that,
dad?

18:20.600 --> 18:22.333
Whatever do you mean?

18:22.435 --> 18:24.702
This is how I talk.

18:24.804 --> 18:26.204
Are you all right, love?

18:27.340 --> 18:30.708
Uh, no.

18:30.810 --> 18:33.244
Have your hot chocolate.
You'll feel better.

18:43.323 --> 18:44.989
This is the best cocoa
I've ever had.

18:45.091 --> 18:46.691
Oh, thanks, dear.

18:46.793 --> 18:48.693
Wait till you try the waffles.

18:48.795 --> 18:50.228
Waffles?

18:58.738 --> 19:00.138
Where am I?

19:03.943 --> 19:05.309
Have a seat, love.

19:07.180 --> 19:09.213
Just the way you like them.

19:13.987 --> 19:17.588
- You guys are punking me.
- We're what now?

19:17.690 --> 19:20.091
This is some kind
of reality show

19:20.193 --> 19:22.426
where you gaslight
the children of divorce

19:22.529 --> 19:25.563
with happiness and everything
they've ever wanted, huh?

19:25.665 --> 19:27.431
Darcy, you're not making
any sense now.

19:27.534 --> 19:30.268
I'm not making any sense?
You guys can't stand each other.

19:30.370 --> 19:31.702
- Where'd you get that now?
- No.

19:31.804 --> 19:34.739
From your divorce!

19:34.841 --> 19:37.475
